column64: The thing we consider a disaster that can harm the world should it enter the world is extreme heat. There is nothing that can happen in the presence of extreme heat. That is because everything that is done needs water, everything that is done requires a supportive weather. Let's say the crops you plant, or even the life of a human being, cannot happen when there is so much heat. You'll find that there is a climate that is favorable for the life of a human being, however, should there be extreme heat, there is nothing that can survive in this world. We see countries abroad where whenever there is extreme heat prevails even for only three months, everything dies beyond salvage. Therefore I think that extreme heat can be a disastrous thing should it happen. It would mean that we forsake farming, we forsake rearing of animals. Ourselves, where will you run for help? That's why I'm saying that if it is to happen then it would be the end of us because everything we help ourselves with comes from the soil. These things come from the soil because they need water, however, how would you farm if there's such drought? Therefore, whenever we see drought, it is like when we see ourselves dying, we are no longer there. Therefore, it is such a scary thing. It would be a disaster should it enter the world. I consider it a very scary thing in the life of a human being. I'll finish there.
column66: Climate change is the difference in the weather patterns. The difference is seen when sometimes there is too much rainfall and sometimes there is drought. If in the past days, a lot of rainfall is experienced and and today there is drought, then I can describe that as climate change. So climate change is when there is a change in the weather patterns from the yesterday and today. We saw climate changing to a point where we cannot predict whether we can have a good or bad harvest. We can experience heavy rains then at the end there is drought and very high temperatures. So we cannot predict how our crops will do if we plant. For the crops to do well, they need at least three months of predictable weather pattern. With the constant weather changes between high rainfall and drought the crops cannot do well. Rainfall is required during planting and weeding and sunshine during harvesting. With the weather changes, we experience sunshine when we need rain and rain when we need sunshine. That is where climate change affect farmers like myself.
column68: Results because of climate change? Should I mention the positive or the negative ? As a result of climate change, our land has died (become desolate). In some instances, climate change has triggered a lot of rainfall to the extent that one can imagine it will never rain again. It rains so much to the point it ruins our walking paths. Sometimes, it rains and floods.  So many people have migrated but some can't migrate because they don't have the finances to do so. That has been climate change. Some people's farms have been washed away by erosion including the very top soil that has humus that has gone with the rainwater. People are forced to farm in barren lands where no crop can produce yields in. Because they were not ready for climate change, it surprised them. They were not aware of it. Climate change has also brought about some new kinds of trees, trees that are not indigenous to this place. I think they have been transferred by the rain water. Even climate change has favoured these trees. Trees we have never seen before. There is a particular one that meanders on the ground and is very thorny. It's a tree that wasn't previously on our land. We can't tell where it is from. Maybe it was brought by moving water or climate change has allowed it to sprout and flourish here. Cows can't graze next to eat because it's very thorny. In fact, cows cannot even put their mouths on the ground if it's around. Climate change has driven us to hunger and we can't predict the climate. You can work really hard thinking that the climate will favour you but eventually, it switches to unfavorable conditions that can't allow our seeds to grow. This has made our farm fields go to waste because we had planted early hoping that the climate would favour what people had planted. Unfortunately, it turned out differently and there are no grains. Some people had tilled, some had planted, and farm fields have gone unplanted because things did not turn out as expected. So that is how climate change has hurt us in another way as per our discussion today.

column33: As it is, right now, what I would wish to change? What I would wish to change is remodel it from a mud-thatched house to a brick-walled house. Because a mud-thatched house requires repairs to the walls after one year and yearly after that. column64: Okay, most of the crops we grow are crops that require a certain duration to grow, for example, maize can be ready within three months of planting. We need rain during planting and weeding, and after that even if it stops raining, the crops will still do well. So at times after planting, just before you finish weeding, it stops raining, which affects the crops, by making them stagnant instead of continuing to grow. This affects farming in that when it was supposed to rain, it does not rain, and thereby the harvest will not be so good, and what was expected to be harvested cannot be achieved. We usually use DAP when planting, however, when it stops raining when you are using DAP, you will have a poor harvest. When the harvest is poor, the price in the market will be higher, yet people don't have money. So when it is at a higher price, other people who cannot afford to buy the maize will be forced to eat other types of food which might not have a balanced diet.  Some people might eat ugali after a week because of lacking money, and others might be forced to take sweet potatoes which are full of starch, and you, therefore, find our bodies lacking essential vitamins. You will find even if someone has money, he/she will buy the maize at a higher price, and not buy other basic needs like clothes, and even at times he/she might leave education aside because food becomes a priority. A lot of money will be used on food, thereby creating an imbalance.
column66: Climate change is the change in rainy seasons. Such that we used to have a rainy season, one for short rains and one for long rains. But there has been a change in climate and the seasons we knew to be for long and short rains have changed. Now the long rainy season which we knew to have a lot of rain, has changed and now the season has little rain now because of the change in the climate. So the things that we had previously planted during the long rains, can no longer be planted because the rains as we were used to, have become less. So things have changed. The season that we knew to have short and little rain, has become the season where we can now start planting. Another thing is that climate change has led to poor harvests. You find that there is so little rain that the grass that cows usually feed on is scarce. But previously, we could predict the weather and we would know the season of long rains would bring a lot of grass for grazing and we were not worried. Right now, you can't reserve land because the place you imagine you will till, you will end up finding out that the rains will not be enough for any harvest. So climate change has affected the estimations we had and spoilt plans.
column68: The way it has affected the community, for example, we were lucky to have One Acre Fund opening one of their shops here. We usually use DAP and CAN to increase the yield of our crops, but their prices skyrocketed, and we still went ahead and bought them at that high price and planted our crops, but then it stopped raining. So the whole community experienced loss, even though people are yet to harvest, you can just see that there is hunger already even if you walk around. Maize which people were relying on, will flower at the height that it has currently reached. We don't have hope that we will harvest anything for sure, and that has affected the community. They have used a lot of money expecting to get a lot of profit, but whatever they will harvest is very little.

column66: What is climate change? I can describe climate change as the abrupt change in weather patterns. There are certain times when we experience the onset of long rains, that is between February and March. This goes on up to July. Climate change delays the start of the rainy season to April or May. We, therefore experience hard times which are brought about by the changes in weather patterns.
column68: The river. There are places where cattle would be taken for watering and which used to have water many times, they are no longer available because they are dry. Also, these days, planting times have changed. You will find that the time when the planting season starts has changed. The time for planting comes late these days. Second, when it rains these days, you realize that it is lower volumes. For example, the rainy season at the start of the year which is called 'chiri' (long rains), lately has low volume rainfall despite being the season that previously had more rainfall. As opposed to these days, during short rains called 'opon' when the rainfall volumes were traditionally lower, now experience the highest rainfall volumes. These days we have wet Christmas all the way to February which should not be the case. You will find that people and things have really changed in our village because of climate change. The foods that we use to depend on like maize, sweet potatoes, cassava, sorghum are nowadays scarce given the scarcity of rainfall. You'll find that the focus has shifted to trees. People have cut down trees. People have ventured into different things like digging the soil to mine gold. Therefore, climate change has really given us problems.
column72: It affected me since I had visitors and who were not comfortable, and it ruined the visit. Then, after my visitors had left, the house was so cold that we had to light a fire so the children could feel warm. It took us about a week of lighting a fire in the house. column66: When thinking of climate change with regards to the past life that humans had, everything is different. In the past when farming we only knew about organic manure that was obtained from the cow dung. Nowadays people have abandoned the  use of cow dung and instead they have gone for inorganic manure. Things that we did in the past or rather things that we ate in the past are not available nowadays. People do not cultivate sorghum or even sweet potatoes. In this present life, our female children, get into a marriage at an early age and get pregnant while young. So that is the climate change that I see in this area. I do not see any thing that was happening in the past happening now.
column68: The reason why it is affecting people, is if we go back to the farm fields, right now, they are not doing well. Because something new has appeared, a weed that we call, Ayongo. column64:
Why are you worried about drought?

I am worried about drought because it can be compared to a barren wife. When it's there, we experience so much suffering because even wild vegetables are nowhere to be found. It consumes everything including animals even the cows we can't eat. But when it rains there's happiness everywhere. I won't even spend my little money because I can get wild vegetables and cook, you understand? Maize does well during the rainy season and I can scoop some from my stock.

That is why I am worried about the barren wife called drought.

Yes.

column66: There is a big change, in the way I am seeing this climate compared to years back, the land used to be fertile but nowadays it is not, if you fail to use fertilizer on your farm then you get a poor harvest. At times also the rains fail to come, and when they come the crops have already failed and this really affects us. Heat has also increased here, in the past, it was never this hot, now you find that it is too hot compared to the previous year, even when I used to be a kid it used to be very cool unlike nowadays. Some weeds have also appeared and we don't know where they have come from, and they are the ones that are now many, and even finding grass is now difficult. They just look like shrubs and they are now many, and our cows can't even feed on them, they are things that don't help us, and they are many on our farms. There are also many worms in our farms such as the fall armyworm, which are destroying maize. There is something called kayongo which has invaded our farms, this kayongo is affecting maize, once it attacks a maize stem, the maize stops growing. It never used to be here but now it is here. Some diseases of banana trees have also appeared, you find that a banana tree grows well, and as soon as it starts fruiting, all the fruits rot, and I think climate change is still responsible for this. Cassavas have also been affected by some diseases, you find the cassava rotting and we don't really know the cause, but I think it is still climate change. In the past, we used to get very big cassava, but nowadays they are small until you can cook them without cutting them into smaller pieces unlike in the past. Nowadays you just have to peel the cassava and cook it because they are too small, and that is the effect of climate change in our surrounding. Another issue is soil erosion, flooding takes away the fertile top soil leaving behind soil that is not fertile which cannot grow crops well, so if you don't use fertilizer there is nothing that you can get from the farm. In the past, we also used to have a lot of streams, but they all dried, and people used to grow sugarcane in those areas, but now you can't grow sugarcane. There are just specific areas where there is a lot of water, but areas that used to grow sugarcane in the past like Odundo nowadays don't grow them. Even if you want to grow Napier grass, it requires where there is water, but getting water is difficult, they all dried up. Trees that used to grow in the past are also not available nowadays.
column68:
In the olden days, people used to keep large heards of cattle. The cows were fat, big and so many. Right now, people have no enough pasture to feed the cows. Animal feeds are not there in the first place. So, it forces people to keep a small number of cows yet still there is no enough pastures for them. It is really different from the past. In the past, milky was there in plenty but nowadays even if you milked a cow, there is no milk in these cows. In the past a cow could produce even 3 jugs of milk, nowadays even a glass does not get filled up. 
Food was plenty in the past. Nowadays food is scarce. Those crops that people used to grow like cassavas, sweet potatoes and such like crops nolonger exists. Only a few people still grow them and still they do not do good like they used to. So, food is scarce. These are a lot of changes already. 
In the past, if yu happen to go to someone's place you would eat a lot of boiled maize nad beans and still leave more there but nowadays food is meaured using spoons. People literally have no food. People are not eating as they used to. There was plenty of water. There was water in all these rivers but now they have since dried up. Nowadays people rely on rains to rain so as to tap rainwater. If that is not the case then you have to find water in the taps. Water in those taps are not free, you have to buy. In the past water was freely accessible.

I have been farming and the climate has changed, now the maize does not grow, the beans also do not ripen. I stopped farming because of climate change because I cannot predict. I know the change of weather has affected me, and in my own words, I see when we don't have rain we always have very hot sun. It affects us in farming. Shrubs are dry, there is no grass, cattles now become thin and they also die because they lack drinking water and there is no grass they can feed on. When a child has been sent home due to school fees, you decide to take one of the cows in the market in order to sell and get some money for school fees. You can not sell the cow in a good price due to its status. The money you get is not even equivalent with the money that was needed in school.

Change of cllimate has also affect us in farming, we can not do farming now because we can not predict when the rain will come and when it will stop so that we can do timing for farming. So we stopped farming.

The change of climate has also affected our income in that you find maybe somebody who wanted you to go and plough for him/her telling you that "let us wait until the time rain will come". The perosn tell you to wait until the time rain will come, when it does not rain you can not get that work. So change of climate has affected us on how to get our income.

The climate changes has really affected us as a community  because in the past, it used to rain and we could get food in good time. This makes the crops to die. If this happens like three times in a single season, when now it decides to rain, you find that you have ran out of seeds because the ones you planted dried up. The climate change has brought even sickness and diseases which we cannot understand. Parasites and insects have made their way to the crops that we consume. We are experiencing a lot of uncertainities and problems. The rain is not raining at the expected time. People have problems in their houses, there is no food in those houses. What I would like is that the corrugated iron sheet on my roof be replaced because it leaks. Also, I would be happy if my house could be plastered in all areas, both the walls and the floor because I did not manage to do every part. I would prefer the use of tiles on the floor, that is because tiles make your work look neat and appealing to the eye. When cleaning your tiled floor, you do not use soap water, but should you do, you should know how to do it to avoid slipping accidents as you say. 
Something else that I would like changed here?...that would be if another house could be built. I would be so happy if a house could be erected for my older son. He has become of age but he has no house. He has been doing some menial jobs around to that effect in vain and as such, it would be a great reprieve if a house can be built for him.
column64: I am afraid of the dry season because when the dry season comes, for example here in our village, you know you cannot harvest anything even if you plant, and there is nothing that you can do, it becomes so hot that there is nowhere to seek shelter, during this time you cannot sleep inside your houses, so people move outside to sleep because of the extreme heat. Due to the dry season, there is also a shortage of water and you know water is the life of a human being.
column66: There has been a change for sure because when we were growing there was a big difference. During that time, by January people would have started planting, and by June the harvest is ready and people would really eat because you could find some ugali remaining near the fireplace and even some maize, but now during harvest, you cannot even find any maize near the fireplace, which means that the climate has changed, life is difficult for people. The soil has also changed such that even if you plant, the harvest is poor. I don't know if it is the soil that is old, I don't know for sure. These things are happening now, it is different from the time when we were growing up.
column68: The difference that I am seeing nowadays, is that nowadays there is a lot of rain, it rains a lot and our crops are not doing well because of too much rain, in the past, around November you could start seeing signs of the dry season and you know it is almost Christmas, it is almost December. So it used to rain occasionally, but nowadays it is too much and there is a difference, and life has also become problematic. I can also add that the population of people living around has increased, people are congested such that there is nowhere to farm, and you can only get a small space to farm that if your harvest is good you can only get three bags. The air quality is also not good because of the congestion, so I think that is also one of the things that are causing climate change.
column77:
We had taken our supper and the young man had gone to sleep when the fire broke out. I was in this house and still awake when the whole thing transpired. It happened that there was another young man that helped himself at my son's house (he used to come to sleep there for lack of a place). Now this boy walked out and locked the door from the outside. My son was a standard eight at that time. We suddenly heard alarms from my son wailing 'mother I'm burning!' It was a grass thatched house. The moment we got out and ran to the scene, opened the door to free him, the roof of the house caved in under the strength of the fire. 
We suspect there was someone outside who lit the fire. The fire razed everything that was in that house including his school uniforms that the only clothes he had left were those on his back. I felt so bad. We looked for policemen who came and arrested the man we suspected to have organized the arson attack. However, shortly after that we later decided to withdraw the case from the police station out of sympathy for the young man. We left him to his guilt and fate. The ordeal hurt me so bad and affected me as much.

In my own words? In my view, life is very difficult these days. Long ago life was easy because you did not need so much to survive, the little you had could get you by but that is not the case as we speak because life is unbearable. The toughness of life has been occasioned by inflation and hard economic times. These days there is lack of money but the value of the shilling has gone high. Therefore, that explains the high cost of living. Long time ago we had little money but there was adequate food, now we have inadequate food. 
We could try employing a few remedies but I doubt we can go back to where we were many years ago. In our attempts to remedy the situation, we can try growing different crops. We should grow sweet potatoes and cassava alongside the conventional maize and other grains so that we have options for food. Additionally, we must also plant trees to improve the climate and attract rainfall.

column64:
I am worried about extreme heat because when it is always sunny then there is always no hope that it is going to rain. 
Secondly people loose motivation for growing crops because they feel like even if they grow crops then they will get destroyed by the extreme heat and so I would not be able to get yields. This is quite worse as compared to an earthquake because an earthquake can occur but still it can rain. But for this situation where It is always just sunny none stop and a person cannot be able to plant anything, I feel worried.  Also the extreme heat  affects the livestock because when you do not farm, you lack green pastures to feed them, the vegetation also is dry and so livestock is forced to survive on water alone. This is really affecting our animals.  When there is no rain you will the animals just licking the soil because there is nothing to feed on. So when there is no rain we are really affected because even the farm produce decreases and becomes less.
Thirdly it makes people lack the incentive to practice crop and animal farming. In the past when there was rain people could even farm prior to the planting season. Because of the extreme heat soil looses its moisture and the minerals get leached and so the soil becomes infertile.
column66:
Climate chnage is the changes of the weather patterns that happen in the atmosphere. You find that in the past like here at our place, we have one planting season. By the time wwe are planting, we plant once. When the change of climate had not occurred, here in our comunity we used to adquate rainfall. The rains that used to rain could support the one planting season. We used to feel that indeed it has rained. But nowadays, when there are rains, people can start preparing their farms in the month of March and still wait upto to May for rains. When it finally rains, it does very shortly. So,  it is so inadequate that cannot make the plants to mature in this area that we live. That is one.
Two, we have short rainfalls, these short rainfalls comes because of climate change. The climate change also is caused by lack of not planting trees because in some days back, there were trees. People have resorted to do deforestation. They could cut tree to make charcoals. So, when people continued cutting trees and making charcoal even on the hills that used to attract rains for us. Here we believe that the hills and the lake are the ones that attracts the rains in this area. When the trees are cut the rains that we expect to rain fails to rain in the expected time. 
Thirdly, you can find that you have planted but it fails to rain completely. The sun shines through out. This therefore will results to low yield. In the end of farming, the farmer gets nothing from the farm because of inadequate rainfall and sun and ecetera. So, these are the situations that I am certain that they have been brought by climate change. You find that the rains that used to rain here, sometimes you see it in the clouds but it passes over to another area. You find that when it passes over this area, it rains in some other areas.
Another one is that sometimes we can stay for long without experiencing the rains. We stay for so long without seeing rains. So if someone wants to plant their vegetables and other crops apart from the main grains like maize, it becomes difficult because if you dont own a water pump or a generator you cannot farm even simple vegatables or even tomatoes because of the climate change. The climate change has affected us adversely because like for me , last year I planted and I did not harvest anything. The crops died in the fam because the rains failed to come. This is a big challenge to us. We have to continue buying foodstuffs because the rains are inadquate. I think so far, that is how I can explain how I understand in terms of Climate Change.
column68:
The way people practice farming is one of the things that have changed as a result of climate change. People cannot till their lands or they cannot prepare their lands earlier the way they used to do it sometimes back. 
Secondly, you may prepare that land waiting for the rainy season, and since I said that the rain is inadequate, you may prepare your land, till your land and plant the seeds and when you are waiting for rainfall to fall, sometimes you may wait for that rainfall and you find yourself in a difficult situation where the rainfall will not be there and you have already used the money had in the preparation and planting and as such will hardly get back the money you invested in the farming at the end of the season. So these are some of the things that transpire these days. 
Secondly, the rains used to come early. Previously, people used to be aware of the fact that the long rains would come in March and because that happens no more, we are affected. The rains that people relied on for the planting season came during March. Unfortunately, these days we cannot plant in March. You will always find that these days people start land preparation in March and wait until the month of May to plant because that is where they expect the rains will fall. So these these things have really affected us. These are the things that have changed about our climate that never used to happen previously. 
The third thing that transpired back in the days but no longer is the case is the fact that the rains would fall for as long as two months non-stop. However, the rains, which by the way are intermittent, can come and fall only for about a month only, and subside significantly during the second month of rainfall when it should boost the crops for better yields. Therefore, these are some of the things we see now that never happened in the past because of climate change. 
Fourth, we used to prepare our lands during the month of December. In fact we would celebrate Christmas with our farms ready for the planting season early in the year. That preparation, however, does not happen these days. Nowadays people are disorganized for lack of knowledge and predictability of what will happen and when. As a result of that, some people will be late in their land preparations, some people will be on time while others might be too early. Some unlucky ones are also caught off guard by the rains before they are ready fro the planting season. These are the effects of the climate change that I see.

column68: A lot of things have changed in our area and even the country at large because of climate change. For instance, there used to be great forest cover in the country, the likes of the Mau Forest, which, it is healthy state made life beautiful for citizens. As a result of the climate change, youths have also been really affected in the way of employment. Given the unpredictability of weather conditions and the rainfall patterns, agricultural practices are hardly profitable anymore. The ensuing drought has condemned most of the young people to the 'boda boda' industry (motorcycle version of public transportation over short distances). Some of the youths also engage in crime for lack of means to earn a living because they cannot no longer depend on rain-fed agriculture. Therefore, the climate change has really affected our region and beyond.

column66:
I would describe it as readying your farm in readiness for the planting season and then the rains fail to come or come late. Last season we planted our crops but the rains disappeared shortly after that. As a result, we look at these things and it is clear to us that things have changed. We are approaching the long rains at the start of the year, however, we have no assurance about whether it will come in time or the sun will still be with us into February and beyond. 
Previously the seasons were quite predictable, we used to start preparing our farms in December and January for the first planting season of the year as we wait for rains in late January or February to plant. However, that has since changed and we cannot really be sure about the timings of the rain. Therefore these are some of the effects of the change in climatic conditions in our region.

column64: I fear flooding for many reasons. It denies me peace so much so that I am always worried whenever I see the clouds heavy with rain. The reason I fear flooding is the kind of soil we have in this area. The soil is so weak that when it rains, it is easily defeated by the water and as such, the water damages our houses. We cannot build toilets here because of that water. Because of the poor soils here, our pit latrines do not last as they always crumble from the inside under the weight of the water-filled soil. As we speak, the few who have toilets around have damaged pit latrines. Our pit latrines are mostly damaged during the rainy season. These are some of the reasons why I fear floods.
column66: About climate change you say? First of all if you change the climate, there is bound to be an onset of different diseases. An example of that change would be when you feel cold as a result of cold climatic conditions in your area.

If fish is not dried then there is no way that we can fry them so we have to wait because if we fry them before they dry then a lot of oil will be consumed. We are forced to leave them up to the next day  for them to dry and after then is when we are able to fry them, this not a good scenario at all.

column64: The reason why I fear an earthquake is when the sky has thunderstorms, don't you know that lightning is a devil? When there are thunderstorms in the sky, it scares people. That's why we fear lightning. It's also something that happens once in a while then you hear that it happened once on another day. So it doesn't happen frequently. That is why people fear lightning because lightning is something that if it enters your house, can carry your house. Either, it can burn your house and yet it has just rained. column66: Life is really hard  for us who work and earn a hundred or fifty shillings a day. I swear sometimes you are always  stranded and you do not know what to do. You buy the flour or borrow it. If you earn fifty then you just  buy a flour that costs fifty shillings and then you prepare porridge for you and the kids to feed on. The cost of life is very high. We are really suffering. We have to pay school fees but we do not have the means and the children have to go to school. Sometimes me together with my kids we always sleep on empty stomachs and in the morning I ask them to drink water and then leave for school. It is by God's grace that we are alive. Other times I boil water and to pour it into the flask for them to drink in the morning and life goes on. Me as  widow I  always go to work where we are tasked with carrying wet sardines. If you have eaten is when you can carry more of this. If you go to work when you have not eaten then you can collapse. I have collapsed in many occasions and I am tired of it. We are dying of hunger. If you go to the lake, what you will find, that you can leave with is nothing, so now they have abandoned their jobs and now they have become bad people. They turn into thieves. So that brings us a lot of suffering and as the people who God has blessed with a big family, you live with your children like someone who is on borrowed life. column66: The change in climate or even the ways of the sun and rain has become a problem and it has become very problematic. It is like when the sun starts to shine it shines till there is nothing you can do. Even just a way of getting vegetables that you can make maize pulp with becomes hard. Even a way of finding that maize pulp is difficult because you planted seeds but the seeds died because of the sun. That has been the negative effect on my life and even the lives of this whole village. That has been a matter that has brought suffering to a point where children find it hard in their school matters. Because even a means of buying a book becomes hard. Finding money becomes hard because of the sun. Then the opportunity you get during the rainy season or even when the rain comes, that can bring help so that the things that have been planted can flourish, doesn't fall. You find again that it can rain so much that we have to move from our lands where we live because we like in a place that is not so good, in an area that is not so well and water floods. So this matter has made us suffer and you find that during the period where it wants to rain a lot until people think that we can get help, you find that the rain falls a lot and the help is no more. Even the things that you have planted, that water carries away. You are forced to start afresh after the rains, like people who have just come into the village from some other village. Those are the burdens and sufferings we go through because of climate change. Exactly.
column68: Climatic change has really affected us. First, most people living along the lake have lost their livestock due to drought. This is because, the cows in search of pasture along the lake shore, end up drowning. The goats die of starvation as they cannot follow the cows into the water. There is a lot of insecurity. Fishing is poor during the hot season and as this is the main occupation of the people on the lake shore, most people find themselves jobless hence they resort to crime. The crime rate has risen and we live in extreme fear. Thuggery is the order of the day and when the criminals strike, it doesn't matter whether you have what they want or not. Everyone is a victim and you can lose your life in the process. There is also a change in the weather patterns. Floods are common during the rainy season. The landscape makes this easy and we risk being swept away. Most times we have to leave our homes and seek shelter in schools. This is quite difficult because at times the school is in session and we inconvenience our children who want to learn and their teachers. It is unfortunate that the few livestock that survived the drought are swept away by the floods. We are therefore always desperate because of the unpredictable climatic change. Both the dry season and the rainy season are extreme hence we are left helpless.
column72: Thank you. Flood as we had spoken in the previous session on the issue of climate change. column33:
These are the reasons I would like to change my house in entirety; First of all the soil we have here is not good quality. The soil is the type that is easily weakened by wetness and therefore it falls down from the walls of my house whenever it rains because the walls were not plastered with cement. As a result of this challenge of weak walls, I have to keep repairing my house by replacing the mud in the destroyed areas after every few episodes of rainfall. 
Additionally, the corrugated iron sheets that were used in making the roof have since grown old under the rust and are leaking. The dilapidated state of my roof forces me to migrate my belongings in the house from other sections to better sections every time it rains. Therefore I do not live a decent life because I lack a good house, I do not like this house. If only I would get another house, I would be very happy because I am tired of the lifestyle here.

column64: I am mostly worried about the rainy season, especially the long rainy one. Whenever it rains in this region, the food waters will come and sweep everything away including the crops in the farms. As such, these events condemn us to life akin to those who live on islands which are prone to flooding. The flooding can sometime last even three months on end. That is why our environment and climatic conditions are not favorable that if I were to find an alternative place, I would really appreciate because nothing good seems to happen for us here. The situation is often so bad that farming is more often than not a futile exercise.  This weather condition has destroyed many of my things. Nothing of mine goes well here.
column66: What I realize with the current climate is that there has been changes in crop production as a result of weather changes. We planted crops last season in time but it is unfortunate that drought came shortly after and destroyed all the crops and therefore had nothing to harvest. Last year we also prepared our farms and planted crops but the rains came and again destroyed everything. The crops were swept away by flood waters and everything ended up in the lake. Where my home is was also totally submerged in the flood waters as the lake broke its banks. As a result of the flooding, I had to migrate to seek refuge in other people's homes which are located on higher grounds. I could not live here for some time. Frankly speaking you would be shocked if you came here in the month of April, we live in a flood prone area and whenever the long rains come, flood water comes from this end and sweeps everything with it into the lake. These are some of the changes I see and which are occasioned by climate change.

column68:
The climate changes we see trouble us as natives of this region. We have many problems especially during the rainy season. Whenever we have the long rains, we are troubled because we keep worrying about the potential of the floods happening. We get so much worried as a result that we lose hope on the crops we have planted the moment the rainy season is here. The crops always get destroyed. 
The food water is also a nuisance because it feels our houses and makes life unbearable. Additionally, we experience hippo attacks as a result of the rains and flooding. The hippos come out of the lake and feed on the crops in our farms and render our farming efforts useless. These are some of the things that trouble us as a result of climate change.
column72: Yes, the flooding affected me. The floods filled up everything, It flooded my crops, the vegetables that I planted were washed away. Also wild animals came. When there is climate change, the weather changes from rainy to sunny, as a result, people know the types of clothing that they should wear during that time period. column66:
Climate is things like rainfall, sunshine, drought and things like that, right? From the way I look at it, I feel like the current weather conditions we are enjoying is good. We can take advantage of the rainfall and plant some vegetables so that by the time the rains disappear, we shall have enough vegetables upon which to feed. Failure to plant the vegetables now will lead o shortage of the same when drought comes. 
For instance if we could plant the likes of 'mitoo' and 'ododo' (traditional vegetable delicacies synonymous with the luo and western tribes), won't we still be able to eat even when the drought is here? I f someone shows up and offers me even fifty shillings to buy soap, wouldn't that be great? Otherwise, we have to work hard. For instance, we are currently planting sweet potatoes.
column68:
Right now there is too much hunger. As we speak right now one tin of maize is retailing at a very high price. One tin of maize goes for eighty shillings yet in the past days it was at fifty shillings. The cost for milling is thirty shillings. Two tins you mill with thirty shillings. Even right now, I am just from the poshomill and I have paid that much. This is what we see as changing in today's life. In the past we used to mill with five shiilings per tin of maize, then later it got to ten shillings per tin. Right now it has changed. Even the price for the maize was equaly lower. In the past you could buy maize at forty shillings or fifty shillings per tin. When I was still a young lady, we could buy it at seventeen shillings. Right now this hunger is too much for us.  Let us get receive food from the west countries. The climate change has brought too much hunger, let us be given some relief food. 
We want seeds that can mature fast and resist climate change. If they are giving us seeds let them give us those that will mature fast so that bu August we will have food otherwise, the  hunger that is anticipated in the future will be oo much. So among the changes, that is what I would say that there is a looming hunger in future.

Apart from the walls, I would change the windows soa s to have different windows than these. I would wish to change the iroon sheets to plus the doors. 
Reason for desiring to chnage the walls is because it is made of mud so everytime I keep on mending the cracks. I would like to change it because it is mud-walled house, I keep on repairing it. 
I would like to change the iron sheets because these ones are 32gauge, instead I would like to have the ones for 30gauge or 28gauge because there are stronger. These ones even when the hails from the raincan break it. That is why I would change them.
The doors should be changed because in this place there are thieves who tries to break into people's houses. These people tries to come when no one is around, breaks in and steal from you. The climate has changed because when we were born here, we had farms to till. But due to urbanization, all the farming land were sold. Because of that, others became squatters. So for one to have farming land you have to find somewhere else to rent. Those who were wise sold theirs and bought land in other places. Okay for climate change, the standard maize 
 the standard seeds, especially maize seeds, if planted brings low yields. This is so even if manure is used.  So we really don't understand where the problem may be. Or maybe it could be because of continuous cultivation. With the hybrid seeds if fertilizers are used one would get high yields even in overly cultivated land. For the standard maize seeds, a little lack of rainfall would kill the crops. A lot of rainfall would also affect them, they become reddish and never get fertilized hence no maize is formed. I really don't understand the cause of climate change, but it has changed. People used to have high yields but that is not the case currently.

column68:
In our village we used to plant even during 'opon' (the second planting season of the year that starts around August/September). However, that has not been the case because we have been farming in vain. We have been preparing our lands and planting crops but unluckily, drought follows and renders our efforts useless. That happened even this time and we got nothing from the farms. As a result of the climate change that has led to the drought and consequently poor crop yields, life became very expensive. We faced serious food shortage and high food prices. 
For instance the price of a 2 kg tin of maize shot to 200 shillings before milling it. Everything skyrocketed as a result and life became unbearable for families. Looking at the price of sugar, we could not afford it due to the same price issue. The smallest packaging of sugar called 'kobole' currently sells at 25 shillings. Using that amount of sugar in this household was not easy, let alone the fact that this household needs half a kilogram of sugar per day which costs 80 shillings. Overall, we had a very difficult time because life was not fair to us.

I think climate change has everything to do with the things we use as human beings and how we use them. We human beings are the reason we have the climate changes we see today. We have defied the things that God commanded us to us and the lifestyle he wanted us to live and devised our own ways of living. It is on these grounds that God chose to punish us in that way. Even when we read the bible, we see that Adam and Eve were punished for disobeying God. As a result of their disobedience, man was condemned to pain when giving birth and having to sweat and toil for his food. Therefore these were consequences of going against the will of God.
The things we see happening now are also because the world is nearing its end. There is nothing that remains of this world. Therefore these are some of the things that God uses to punish the human race for its sins. God is making life difficult for man that he may repent and make his ways with God right before the world ends and we still defy the call. It is for these reasons that God is using the climate change to punish the human race.

Second, the land has become very hot with excess heat. In the past, we used to know that it is only hot in Mombasa but right now just here in Rarieda, here in Siaya, the land is excessively hot. It is becoming unbearable. 
The current rains seasons are slo not like the former rains seasosns. They are changed rain seasons. We farm in the month of April expecting that it will rain, only for the rains to miss. When the rains finally come, the crops are already destroyed by the sun. That is the third changes we have experienced due to climate change.
I will stop there.

column66:
Climate change has brought a huge problem to our country. Climate change has changed rainfall patterns and as a result, the days the rains come without people expecting it to come when it comes. At the same time, it does not rain when we expect it. The climatic changes have disrupted and disorganized farmers so much that we no longer can predict when to prepare our lands in readiness for the planting seasons. These days we cannot be sure whether to plant in February or April. 
I am not sure what has really caused the climate to change. It could be that we have cut down too many trees or that we have failed to plant enough trees, either way something is wring. All these things have really made life difficult for us here. We work so hard in the farms and when time for harvesting comes, we have nothing to show for it given our investment and efforts. The results of the climate change in our region is drought which has brought famine and poverty.

In the past, it rained a lot and it came at the right time, and we were used to that time, but now things have changed, we are not sure of what will happen if you plant, you just plant and you don't know if it will ripen or die, now we are just using our energy for nothing and there is no income.

column33:
At this time if I could get my hands on 25 pieces of corrugated iron sheet, I would be really happy because I will use them to replace the roofing. Also, the iron sheets will give me an opportunity to construct a separate kitchen to avoid cooking that goes on in this house. The soot that comes from the kitchen has affected the roof and contributes to its short life span. When done, these changes would really give me a good life. However, if the condition of the house remains as is with the ensuing wear and tear, one day when it rains or when the is strong sun, the roof will develop holes and start leaking and that would be a disaster for me. 
Also, were it not for the challenge of inadequate funds, I would consider changing the roofing timber as the corrugated iron sheets are being changed. The walls of the house can also be improved by insertion of some bricks all around it that even without it being plastered, the strength of the house will be improved to avoid damage that might be caused by strong winds, otherwise, the house as is is so weak that one of these days it might be destroyed and blown away by wind because it has been weakened by termite infestation over time.
column64: Climate change can really affect us because we are people who are just starting a new life. At a time when there is floods, the water washes up everything on it's way and disposes it all into Lake Victoria which goes on to the red sea. Thus once it has passed by it leaves with everything and forces you to start afresh. Which means the rivers have over filled the banks and it flows with so much force and in different tides. As for the extreme sun heat, we can plant more trees that can control the heat.
column66:
About climate change, I would say that first of all a long time ago during the 70s and the 80s, we could farm and plant our crops without using the fertilizers and we still realized good crop yields. However that is not the case these days as you have to have some artificial fertilizer manufactured by the white man for you to get some harvest from the farms. 
Also, the large human population ahs also led to deforestation. It is possible to find that someone will fell down five trees at a go and fail to plant even one as replacement and that has changed a lot of things in the atmosphere. The results of such wanton cutting down down of trees has even affected the quality of the air we breath because it has been compromised. 
Additionally if we reflect back, we could use our energy to till the land ourselves and do everything else without machines but that has since changed as well, we no longer have the energy to do that and the soils have also become harder for our bare strengths. It is for that reason that these days people will resort to using tractors to plough and plant using artificial farm inputs. It would be interesting to note that just a few years back, farming was not a difficult task provided we had food to give us energy and cow dung to be used as fertilizer for the crops. 
These days the human farmer population has also become selective in what they grow as food crops. Most farmers in this area have focused on maize and neglected the farming of sorghum, sweet potatoes and cassavas. Noteworthy, someone who feeds on ugali prepared with a mixture of sorghum, maize and cassava will have better health outcomes and strength compared to one who does not. If subjected to tests by the doctor, the person who feeds in a well balanced diet containing the aforementioned grain combination will have strong immunity against diseases as a result of the active white blood cells. It is unfortunate that these days people do not adhere much to balanced diet because of food shortage occasioned by climate change.
